The paper discusses the use of ontologies and scenario-based approaches for the development of automated vehicles, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also emphasizes the importance of safety analysis and comprehensive testing, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the need for an economical test and release process, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
